COPS are looking for two suspects after a 15-year-old girl was raped by two men in Wesselsbron, near Bothaville in the Free State on 4 January 2020. The Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit said the victim was walking from her friend’s place to her home when she was approached by two unknown men. “They allegedly grabbed her and threatened to kill her if she screams. They took her to a bridge that’s not too far from a graveyard and took turns raping her,” said police spokeswoman Sergeant Sinah Mpakane. ALSO READ | THUMBS HORROR ATTACK - They also wanted my 4-5! A case of rape was then registered at Wesselsbron Police Station. Both suspects are still at large. Mpakane urged anyone with information that can help trace the suspects to contact Detective Warrant Officer Moyane Monei on 083 533 6375, or call CrimeStop on 08600 10111.